WEBVTT

00:10.552 --> 00:11.720
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:11.720 --> 00:13.722
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:13.722 --> 00:16.350
♪ Yo! So, it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.350 --> 00:17.809
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.809 --> 00:21.730
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.730 --> 00:23.273
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.774 --> 00:25.692
♪ Stand up and sing along ♪

00:25.692 --> 00:27.611
♪ All different voices
Everybody now! ♪

00:27.611 --> 00:29.321
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.321 --> 00:30.948
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.198 --> 00:33.158
♪ Yeah, we're livin' In harmony ♪

00:33.158 --> 00:36.912
♪ Our song is much stronger
With every Troll singing ♪

00:36.912 --> 00:39.581
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:44.586 --> 00:47.548
‐ Reporters, by starting
this printing press,

00:47.548 --> 00:49.341
we will officially begin publishing

00:49.341 --> 00:52.928
TrollsTopia's first ever
scrapbook‐newspaper,

00:53.512 --> 00:54.763
The Fabloid!

00:54.763 --> 00:57.307
[ Trolls cheering ]

00:57.307 --> 00:58.767
‐ Thanks to our reporting,

00:58.767 --> 01:02.354
all Trolls will finally get recognized
for their fabulous deeds,

01:02.354 --> 01:04.773
which they would never
brag about themselves.

01:04.773 --> 01:06.942
Y'know, 'cuz Trolls are so humble.

01:07.109 --> 01:08.652
‐ No. Stop it!

01:08.986 --> 01:10.946
‐ Poppy, you're the humble one.

01:11.113 --> 01:14.116
‐ Aw, you guys, no, you are.

01:14.116 --> 01:15.659
[ everybody talking ]

01:15.659 --> 01:17.786
Stop! You're the humble one.

01:17.786 --> 01:19.580
[ everybody talking ]

01:19.788 --> 01:23.375
‐ Enough! Ugh!
You're all humble, ok?

01:23.917 --> 01:26.920
POPPY: Aww, Branch…
‐ No, you are.

01:26.920 --> 01:28.880
‐ Gah! Just start the presses!

01:30.299 --> 01:31.508
Oh!

01:32.801 --> 01:35.804
♪

01:37.806 --> 01:39.224
‐ Stop the presses!

01:39.224 --> 01:40.142
[ Trolls gasp ]

01:40.517 --> 01:41.518
‐ Ugh.

01:43.353 --> 01:46.940
‐ Apologies, but I just broke a story
that you need to see!

01:48.150 --> 01:50.819
‐ Minuet is the one
who has been giving out cookies

01:50.819 --> 01:52.446
while Trolls' backs are turned?

01:52.779 --> 01:53.655
[ Minuet giggles ]

01:54.197 --> 01:58.869
Wow, this is front page material, Laguna.
I can see it now:

01:58.869 --> 02:02.831
Minuet Makes Mystery Munchies,
Motivating Many to Mutter.

02:02.831 --> 02:03.957
Mmmm…

02:04.291 --> 02:07.627
‐ No, that headline is way too long‐‐
‐ Start the presses!

02:10.881 --> 02:14.968
‐ Hey, hey, TrollsTopia,
time to get that paper!

02:15.927 --> 02:16.970
Bless up!

02:17.429 --> 02:18.472
One love!

02:19.765 --> 02:20.682
Stay cool!

02:23.352 --> 02:25.854
‐ That's who's been giving out
all those cookies?

02:26.021 --> 02:27.397
Thank you, Minuet…

02:27.856 --> 02:28.732
[ Minuet giggles ]

02:29.900 --> 02:31.610
…wherever you are.

02:31.610 --> 02:32.402
[ Troll laughs ]

02:32.402 --> 02:34.488
‐ I've been waiting
my whole life for this.

02:34.488 --> 02:37.282
‐ Well, the first Fabloid issue
is a big success,

02:37.282 --> 02:38.617
thanks to you, Laguna.

02:38.825 --> 02:41.912
‐ Oh, just wait 'til you see
my next story.

02:42.245 --> 02:45.624
It's about the TrollsTopia Wishing Well.

02:46.500 --> 02:48.835
We are all familiar
with the well tradition…

02:49.044 --> 02:52.589
Trolls toss cupcakes
into the well, make wishes,

02:53.215 --> 02:55.884
and sometimes the wishes
magically come true.

02:55.884 --> 02:57.094
[ Troll cheering ]

02:57.427 --> 03:00.639
But what if the well isn't magic at all?

03:01.598 --> 03:05.060
What if it's a Troll
who's granting those wishes?

03:05.227 --> 03:08.105
A Troll who deserves recognition.

03:09.147 --> 03:12.526
‐ I dunno, Laguna. I've heard
enough wish‐come‐true stories

03:12.526 --> 03:16.029
to think that there really is
something magical about this well.

03:16.029 --> 03:20.909
‐ Please, what possible evidence is there
for the existence of "magic"?

03:21.284 --> 03:22.661
BOTH:
Uh…

03:22.911 --> 03:23.912
‐ Ha.

03:23.912 --> 03:24.996
Ho!

03:24.996 --> 03:25.956
Yeah!

03:26.957 --> 03:29.918
♪

03:33.338 --> 03:35.924
NARRATOR:
<i>"Magic is real!"</i>

03:36.883 --> 03:38.927
‐ Hmm, I see your point.

03:38.927 --> 03:42.931
But, in the case of the well,
I am certain there's a Troll behind it.

03:43.432 --> 03:45.350
And I'm going to prove it!

03:46.893 --> 03:50.272
‐ Suit yourself!
‐ We just hate for you to waste your time.

03:50.272 --> 03:51.356
[ Poppy giggles ]

03:51.815 --> 03:53.066
BOTH:
She knows!

03:56.194 --> 03:57.904
‐ Well, it's all over now!

03:58.071 --> 04:00.115
Laguna's a great reporter, Poppy.

04:00.115 --> 04:02.409
It's only a matter of time
before she exposes

04:02.409 --> 04:05.203
that we're the ones down
in this well granting wishes!

04:06.413 --> 04:07.289
POPPY:
No!

04:07.289 --> 04:09.207
Branch, you've seen the Trolls' faces

04:09.207 --> 04:12.127
when they believe their wish
was granted magically.

04:12.127 --> 04:14.963
It fills them with a hope
that anything is possible.

04:15.088 --> 04:17.757
‐ You're right.
We can't let that be ruined.

04:18.717 --> 04:22.763
'Cuz of the hope thing you just said,
not 'cuz I get cupcakes whenever I want.

04:22.763 --> 04:23.680
[ Branch giggles ]

04:23.680 --> 04:25.932
TINY:
I wish I had a new bike!

04:25.932 --> 04:27.601
‐ Oh! Oh!

04:27.601 --> 04:30.312
♪

04:30.312 --> 04:32.147
So how do we stop Laguna?

04:32.147 --> 04:33.231
‐ Easy…

04:33.231 --> 04:34.524
we keep her busy.

04:36.193 --> 04:38.069
Right after we get Tiny a new bike!

04:38.069 --> 04:39.988
[ both laughing ]

04:40.155 --> 04:43.241
Laguna, we know that you want to work
on that wishing well story,

04:43.241 --> 04:46.620
and while we wish you well,
pun intended,

04:47.204 --> 04:50.332
there's actually a hot new story
that we need you to crack.

04:50.749 --> 04:52.125
‐ What came first,

04:52.584 --> 04:56.171
the chicken bug
or the chicken bug egg?

04:57.088 --> 04:59.633
‐ You want me to answer
a timeless riddle

04:59.633 --> 05:02.803
that's plagued Trolls‐kind
for thousands of years?

05:02.969 --> 05:04.429
BOTH:
Could you?

05:05.180 --> 05:10.185
‐ Well, it seems an odd subject
for a good‐deed based publication,

05:10.560 --> 05:13.814
but if that's my assignment, then…
Hmm…

05:13.814 --> 05:17.150
Trolly moley where does one even begin?
Think, Laguna.

05:17.442 --> 05:18.401
[ Poppy laughing ]

05:18.401 --> 05:21.196
‐ No Troll could ever
answer that question.

05:21.196 --> 05:24.866
‐ Yup, she'll be busy
for a very long time…

05:24.866 --> 05:26.409
[ both laughing ]

05:26.785 --> 05:27.994
‐ It was the chicken.

05:28.995 --> 05:29.996
BOTH:
What?

05:30.121 --> 05:33.208
‐ You were only gone ten minutes!
‐ How did you do that?

05:33.291 --> 05:34.668
‐ It wasn't easy.

05:34.668 --> 05:38.129
<i>I had to brush up on the genetics</i>
<i>of domesticated fowl,</i>

05:38.129 --> 05:42.050
<i>locate a dozen scrolls of knowledge</i>
<i>that had been lost for generations.</i>

05:42.050 --> 05:43.051
Ah!

05:43.051 --> 05:46.638
<i>Decipher three ancient languages</i>
<i>each more complex than the last,</i>

05:46.888 --> 05:47.764
<i>snack break,</i>

05:47.764 --> 05:51.101
<i>and finally submit my findings</i>
<i>to the scientific community</i>

05:51.101 --> 05:52.227
<i>for a strict peer review.</i>

05:52.435 --> 05:53.562
Woohoo!

05:53.854 --> 05:56.064
‐ You did all that in ten minutes?

05:56.064 --> 05:57.232
‐ Oh, no.

05:57.315 --> 05:59.693
I also wrote a draft
of my wishing well article.

05:59.901 --> 06:00.694
BOTH:
Huh?

06:01.111 --> 06:03.738
‐ I have yet to identify
the Troll responsible,

06:03.738 --> 06:06.241
but it details my theory quite clearly.

06:06.533 --> 06:07.701
‐ Wow. We'd…

06:08.118 --> 06:10.120
We'd love to print this, Laguna.

06:10.954 --> 06:11.955
But…

06:12.330 --> 06:15.083
The Fabloid has
certain journalistic standards.

06:15.542 --> 06:16.459
Right, Branch?

06:16.668 --> 06:17.836
‐ Standards.

06:18.086 --> 06:19.045
‐ We need hard facts.

06:19.045 --> 06:22.716
And since your wishing well article
doesn't have an eyewitness…

06:23.258 --> 06:25.135
‐ Oh, I see…

06:25.886 --> 06:27.220
If I had known the standards,

06:27.429 --> 06:30.307
I would've never brought you this
without an eyewitness.

06:30.307 --> 06:31.725
Hmm…

06:32.726 --> 06:33.518
[ both gasp ]

06:34.102 --> 06:35.729
I found an eyewitness!

06:35.729 --> 06:36.897
BOTH:
What?

06:39.357 --> 06:43.653
‐ A few days ago I came to the well
to wish for a new pie,

06:43.653 --> 06:45.780
because someone sat on my old pie.

06:45.780 --> 06:47.866
And I don't want to name names,

06:48.950 --> 06:49.910
but it was me.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.202
[ Cooper laughing ]

06:52.120 --> 06:54.331
Anyway, when I looked down,

06:54.331 --> 06:58.918
I could barely see a Troll
inside the well!

06:59.419 --> 07:01.421
And they were listening to me!

07:02.130 --> 07:04.341
‐ There you have it, an eyewitness.

07:04.341 --> 07:07.761
I believe my story meets
The Fabloid's standards now, yes?

07:08.178 --> 07:09.971
‐ Uh…
‐ Uh…

07:09.971 --> 07:11.765
Well, let's see about that…

07:12.182 --> 07:15.769
Cooper, would you say you're as confident
you saw someone in the well

07:15.769 --> 07:18.938
as you were when you witnessed
that mysterious Troll

07:18.938 --> 07:21.232
that kept following you
everywhere you went?

07:21.232 --> 07:22.317
‐ Oh, absolutely.

07:22.317 --> 07:23.610
But shh…

07:24.027 --> 07:26.279
he's right behind me.

07:28.156 --> 07:30.533
Ooh, you ominous yet
handsome‐shaped Troll!

07:30.742 --> 07:32.744
Why are you so obsessed with me?

07:33.036 --> 07:36.373
Huh? Hey! Don't walk away from me
when I'm talking to you!

07:36.373 --> 07:37.374
Come back here!

07:37.374 --> 07:42.087
‐ Oh my, perhaps Cooper is not
a reliable witness after all.

07:42.295 --> 07:46.466
I'm beginning to doubt whether my article
will ever meet the Fabloid's standards.

07:46.925 --> 07:48.009
Hmm…

07:48.677 --> 07:49.594
[ both sigh ]

07:50.512 --> 07:53.223
‐ Well, Branch,
now that we've taken care of Laguna,

07:53.223 --> 07:54.724
we can finally get back to‐‐

07:55.141 --> 07:56.309
Laguna?

07:56.309 --> 07:57.936
‐ Hello! Just finishing up!

07:58.144 --> 07:59.354
BOTH:
Finishing up?

08:01.064 --> 08:03.942
‐ "Wishing Well Wishes Point
to One Wonderful Troll?"

08:04.359 --> 08:05.443
The Guna Gazette?

08:06.194 --> 08:09.406
‐ Yes! Since my story didn't meet
the Fabloid's standards,

08:09.406 --> 08:11.950
I decided to publish my own paper!

08:12.158 --> 08:12.951
[ both gasp ]

08:13.243 --> 08:17.038
Quickly, Tiny!
TrollsTopia needs to read this right away!

08:17.288 --> 08:19.332
‐ No sweat, amphibious‐Troll lady!

08:19.582 --> 08:23.378
Tiny Diamond's new bike
will make that route in record time!

08:23.586 --> 08:24.421
Ha‐ha!

08:24.421 --> 08:26.256
‐ We've gotta stop those papers!

08:27.382 --> 08:28.925
♪ Hurry up now ♪

08:28.925 --> 08:30.969
♪ We've got to beat the clock ♪

08:31.177 --> 08:33.054
♪ The train's leaving the station ♪

08:33.054 --> 08:35.348
♪ And we can't let them take off ♪

08:35.515 --> 08:37.767
♪ No, keep the cat in the bag ♪

08:37.767 --> 08:39.853
♪ Ooh, we gotta bury the rag ♪

08:39.853 --> 08:41.855
♪ Ooh, or it's gonna be bad ♪

08:41.855 --> 08:44.190
♪ So let's get moving
'Fore they understand ♪

08:44.190 --> 08:46.234
♪ Let's stop the presses ♪

08:46.568 --> 08:48.403
♪ Ring the bell ♪

08:48.695 --> 08:50.030
♪ I confess ♪

08:50.030 --> 08:52.824
♪ It's not gonna end well ♪

08:53.074 --> 08:54.868
♪ Stop the presses ♪

08:55.285 --> 08:57.120
♪ Blow the horn ♪

08:57.454 --> 08:58.496
♪ You could guess ♪

08:58.496 --> 09:01.624
♪ It's worse than I could warn ♪

09:01.624 --> 09:03.209
‐ Yeah! Ah!
‐ Ah!

09:03.209 --> 09:05.420
♪ Stop the presses! ♪♪

09:08.048 --> 09:09.549
LAGUNA:
Poppy? Branch?

09:09.549 --> 09:10.341
[ both gasp ]

09:11.342 --> 09:13.970
You've been taking my papers?

09:14.387 --> 09:15.555
But why?

09:16.556 --> 09:17.974
Unless…

09:18.683 --> 09:19.684
[ Laguna gasps ]

09:19.893 --> 09:21.019
It's you!

09:21.227 --> 09:23.354
You're the Trolls granting the wishes!

09:23.605 --> 09:25.523
‐ Wait, Laguna, listen, we‐‐

09:25.523 --> 09:28.485
‐ No! No more diversions!

09:28.485 --> 09:31.446
I am going to write a new story
that will expose you

09:31.446 --> 09:33.281
for exactly who you are.

09:34.365 --> 09:37.243
Two very sweet Trolls.

09:39.496 --> 09:40.413
[ both sigh ]

09:41.956 --> 09:44.292
TINY:
It's the "Guna Gazette", comin' atcha!

09:47.462 --> 09:49.047
‐ Well, this is it.

09:49.464 --> 09:50.715
Once everyone reads this,

09:50.715 --> 09:53.885
the Trolls' world becomes
a little less whimsical.

09:55.637 --> 09:58.264
"Wishing Well Wishes Point
To Two Terrific Trolls,

09:58.848 --> 10:00.141
by Laguna Tidepool.

10:00.642 --> 10:02.352
Contrary to the common belief

10:02.352 --> 10:05.355
in The TrollsTopia Wishing Well's
supernatural powers,

10:05.355 --> 10:08.316
it was discovered yesterday
that the wishes made at the well

10:08.316 --> 10:11.945
have actually been granted by two Trolls:
Poppy and Branch.

10:12.195 --> 10:12.987
[ Branch gasps ]

10:12.987 --> 10:16.491
The duo's deeds were conducted secretly,
in order to preserve

10:16.491 --> 10:18.910
every Trolls‐Topian's sense
of childlike wonder,

10:19.077 --> 10:22.956
making Poppy and Branch
all the more deserving of recognition.

10:24.165 --> 10:25.083
But…"

10:25.542 --> 10:26.459
‐ But…

10:27.710 --> 10:31.131
‐ "But after a great deal of reflection,
this reporter has decided

10:31.131 --> 10:33.967
that exposing them
would undermine their generosity.

10:34.467 --> 10:37.720
As such, only one copy
of this paper has been printed

10:38.263 --> 10:40.682
and once Poppy and Branch
stop reading it out loud,

10:40.932 --> 10:43.977
Laguna will destroy it
so their secret is kept forever.

10:44.477 --> 10:47.564
By the way, you can look up now,
I'm standing right in front of you?"

10:48.398 --> 10:49.482
BOTH:
Laguna?

10:49.983 --> 10:52.777
‐ You're not going to share
the story with TrollsTopia?

10:53.319 --> 10:54.571
‐ No, I'm not.

10:54.737 --> 10:58.408
All I want is for Trolls to be recognized
for their good deeds.

10:58.825 --> 10:59.784
And now…

11:00.827 --> 11:01.953
you have been.

11:02.370 --> 11:03.413
BOTH:
Aww.

11:05.415 --> 11:07.959
‐ Now, for my next Fabloid story.

11:08.334 --> 11:11.129
I just heard a rumor
that R&B have opened a bed in breakfast

11:11.129 --> 11:13.089
as a place for Trolls to relax!

11:13.423 --> 11:14.215
[ Poppy gasps ]

11:14.215 --> 11:17.093
‐ R&B Open B&B for R&R?

11:17.218 --> 11:18.928
‐ Can you cover it, Laguna?

11:18.928 --> 11:21.973
‐ For a story like that,
we're gonna need our very best!

11:22.390 --> 11:26.186
‐ The best? Oh, stop.
You two are the best.

11:26.186 --> 11:28.605
‐ No, you are! You're the best.

11:28.771 --> 11:31.608
‐ Let's be serious,
you clearly are the best.

11:31.608 --> 11:33.276
‐ You're the best.
‐ Oh, no, you.

11:33.276 --> 11:35.403
‐ Pff, no, you are.
‐ Stop!

11:35.403 --> 11:38.031
‐ Gah!
‐ I won't listen for another second.

11:43.578 --> 11:44.621
‐ Y'see?

11:46.247 --> 11:48.458
It always goes back to a smile.

11:49.417 --> 11:50.376
Told ya, Poppy.

11:50.710 --> 11:53.213
You've got "Resting Nice Face."

11:53.421 --> 11:54.380
‐ Aww.

11:54.380 --> 11:55.381
[ alarm ]

11:55.381 --> 11:56.549
[ both gasp ]

11:56.549 --> 11:58.718
BOTH:
It's time for R&B's podcast!

11:58.718 --> 12:00.345
‐ Yeah!

12:04.557 --> 12:08.519
‐ Live from inside a hair pod,
it's your favorite podcast:

12:09.229 --> 12:10.980
BOTH:
R&B are on it!

12:11.272 --> 12:12.649
‐ I'm your co‐host, R.

12:12.649 --> 12:15.443
And always by my side
is my scintillating sister

12:15.443 --> 12:17.612
from the same mister… B!

12:17.612 --> 12:20.657
‐ Before we bring the funk,
let's have a word from our sponsor.

12:21.532 --> 12:24.661
<i>Today's episode is brought to you by Hugs.</i>
<i>And The Fun Factory‐‐</i>

12:24.661 --> 12:26.663
‐ Hey, mind turnin' it up, bro?

12:26.663 --> 12:27.872
B:
<i>…game‐related needs.</i>

12:27.872 --> 12:31.042
<i>The Funtime Factory,</i>
<i>official sponsor of hide 'n seek!</i>

12:31.542 --> 12:34.212
R: <i>Well, sis,</i>
<i>it's time to open up those vines</i>

12:34.212 --> 12:36.839
<i>and provide our listeners</i>
<i>with the advice they need.</i>

12:37.257 --> 12:38.049
B:
<i>That's right.</i>

12:38.049 --> 12:42.595
Years of scientific study have taught us
that every problem has a solution.

12:42.595 --> 12:44.597
And we're here to help you find it!

12:44.973 --> 12:46.599
‐ Hello? You're on the hair.

12:46.891 --> 12:50.103
‐ Yeah, so, I'm having an issue
with my pet snake,

12:50.103 --> 12:53.523
half the time I pick him up,
he makes this aggressive hissing sound.

12:53.523 --> 12:54.691
So I was wondering…

12:55.316 --> 12:57.902
How do I get him to do it all the time?

12:58.695 --> 12:59.529
R:
Ok…

12:59.529 --> 13:01.489
Unusual question, but…

13:01.489 --> 13:03.324
BOTH:
R&B are on it!

13:04.367 --> 13:06.035
‐ According to our calculations,

13:06.035 --> 13:10.164
you should spend exactly two minutes a day
telling him how much you love his voice

13:10.164 --> 13:14.127
‐ and bam!
‐ The rest is Hissstory!

13:14.419 --> 13:15.295
Next caller!

13:15.837 --> 13:17.297
‐ Hi, um…

13:17.297 --> 13:18.798
my name is, uh…

13:19.132 --> 13:20.091
"Brinch."

13:20.091 --> 13:23.636
What do you do
if the zipper gets stuck on your…

13:24.470 --> 13:25.513
bunny pajamas?

13:25.847 --> 13:26.806
‐ That's easy.

13:26.931 --> 13:29.559
Just jiggle the zipper up up‐down…

13:29.726 --> 13:31.102
‐ Then up‐down‐down.

13:31.269 --> 13:32.061
[ zipper sound ]

13:32.061 --> 13:34.272
BRANCH:
<i>Phew! Thanks, R&B!</i>

13:34.480 --> 13:37.108
BOTH: You're welcome, Branch!
BRANCH: <i>Uh, it's, uh…</i>

13:37.108 --> 13:37.984
<i>Brinch.</i>

13:38.526 --> 13:39.736
BOTH:
Next caller!

13:40.570 --> 13:41.654
‐ Apologize.

13:41.654 --> 13:43.114
‐ And offer to replace it.

13:43.698 --> 13:44.657
‐ Whatever you do…

13:44.866 --> 13:46.325
‐ Don't pull on the gum.

13:46.701 --> 13:47.577
‐ Oh!

13:47.869 --> 13:50.705
‐ So, I said yes to both parties.

13:50.997 --> 13:53.666
But I can't be in two places at once!

13:53.666 --> 13:54.709
‐ You can!

13:54.709 --> 13:56.335
‐ If you let us clone you!

13:56.335 --> 13:57.462
‐ You can do that?

13:57.670 --> 13:59.714
♪

13:59.964 --> 14:00.757
[ Cooper gasps ]

14:00.757 --> 14:03.634
I shall call you Two‐per!

14:03.885 --> 14:05.845
[ Cooper laughs ]

14:06.554 --> 14:09.599
‐ Joining us now, in person, Biggie!

14:09.599 --> 14:11.476
I understand you need help?

14:11.684 --> 14:12.560
‐ Yes.

14:12.560 --> 14:16.731
As you know, Mr. Dinkles and I
recently celebrated our friend‐iversary

14:16.731 --> 14:20.401
and, well, we received a present
from a certain Troll,

14:20.401 --> 14:21.611
which turned out to be…

14:22.570 --> 14:23.571
a re‐gift.

14:24.155 --> 14:25.198
[ both gasp ]

14:25.198 --> 14:27.658
‐ A Troll took a present
they were gifted

14:27.784 --> 14:30.995
and gave it to someone else
in the guise of a new gift?

14:31.162 --> 14:32.246
‐ I'm afraid so.

14:32.789 --> 14:33.581
‐ Ah!

14:34.624 --> 14:35.792
‐ Rest assured, Biggie…

14:35.792 --> 14:37.710
BOTH:
R&B are on it!

14:38.002 --> 14:41.214
‐ That's right! Clearly the solution
to your problem is…

14:41.547 --> 14:43.007
Just let it go!

14:43.007 --> 14:45.176
‐ Confront the re‐gifting Troll!

14:46.427 --> 14:48.221
BOTH:
What?

14:49.514 --> 14:50.765
‐ Uh…

14:50.765 --> 14:52.892
aren't you supposed to say
the same thing?

14:54.894 --> 14:56.187
‐ Yes, we are.

14:56.521 --> 14:57.563
What is happening?

14:58.481 --> 14:59.649
Are we disagreeing?

14:59.649 --> 15:01.150
‐ Apparently so.

15:01.776 --> 15:02.777
And I don't like it!

15:03.611 --> 15:05.655
‐ Biggie, the re‐gift upset you.

15:05.988 --> 15:09.075
The only way to fix this
is to express your feelings

15:09.408 --> 15:10.868
to the Troll in question.

15:11.202 --> 15:13.246
‐ Hmm, I suppose that's true.

15:13.496 --> 15:15.248
I think I will discuss it with them.

15:16.249 --> 15:17.208
‐ Biggie, no!

15:17.208 --> 15:21.838
This Troll likely meant no offense
and a confrontation would embarrass them.

15:22.130 --> 15:26.801
The only way to fix this
is for you to let it go!

15:27.176 --> 15:28.469
‐ Yes.

15:28.636 --> 15:31.639
I guess it would be better
if I gave them the benefit of the doubt.

15:31.639 --> 15:32.682
‐ No!

15:33.224 --> 15:36.227
This is about open
and honest communication.

15:36.644 --> 15:39.438
Whaaa!
‐ Some things are better left unsaid.

15:40.690 --> 15:41.482
Whaaa!

15:41.691 --> 15:43.442
‐ You deserve an explanation.

15:44.527 --> 15:45.778
‐ It's no big deal!

15:46.237 --> 15:47.822
‐ Ah! This is too much!

15:47.822 --> 15:51.784
There's got to be a better way
for me to decide whose advice to take!

15:52.034 --> 15:54.453
♪

15:54.453 --> 15:55.663
‐ Ok! We need data,

15:55.997 --> 15:57.874
now that we're no longer on the air,

15:57.874 --> 16:00.084
tell us what happened
and give us all the details.

16:00.293 --> 16:03.296
‐ Well, it was yesterday. 4:32 pm.

16:03.671 --> 16:08.176
I had just used the process of elimination
to determine who gave us our last gift,

16:08.176 --> 16:12.638
because the tag fell off
when Mr. Dinkles tried to eat it.

16:12.847 --> 16:17.768
Which is a terrible habit of his
and gives him the worst indigestion, but‐‐

16:17.768 --> 16:20.229
‐ Uh… Maybe not all the details.

16:20.646 --> 16:21.814
‐ Oh, right.

16:21.814 --> 16:22.690
[ Biggie giggles ]

16:22.690 --> 16:23.733
Anyway…

16:23.816 --> 16:24.942
It was from Dante.

16:25.359 --> 16:26.485
[ both gasp ]

16:26.485 --> 16:27.695
BOTH:
Dante?

16:27.695 --> 16:28.487
‐ Yes.

16:28.487 --> 16:31.324
And when I opened it,
I found the exact cupcake dome

16:31.324 --> 16:35.036
that I'd given to him to congratulate him
at his big concert last week.

16:35.494 --> 16:39.165
‐ Got it. Now, using
some super‐funky predictive modeling,

16:39.373 --> 16:42.710
I have mathematic certainty
that by taking my advice

16:42.710 --> 16:45.755
and confronting Dante,
it'd go like this.

16:48.674 --> 16:49.675
‐ My word, Biggie.

16:50.009 --> 16:52.845
Thank you for bringing
this Trolls‐pas to my attention!

16:53.346 --> 16:55.306
It never occurred to me that a re‐gift

16:55.306 --> 16:57.725
could so affect the feelings
of a fellow Troll.

16:59.518 --> 17:02.688
I swear to you, from now on,
I will do better.

17:02.939 --> 17:04.941
‐ Oh, my! That went well!

17:04.941 --> 17:06.484
‐ It sure did.

17:06.776 --> 17:09.820
And once that happens,
who knows what it could lead to…

17:10.321 --> 17:13.616
‐ And the Trolls‐bel Peace Prize
goes to…

17:13.824 --> 17:15.618
Dante Crescendo!

17:15.618 --> 17:17.203
[ applause ]

17:18.621 --> 17:19.872
‐ I know it's a cliche,

17:20.081 --> 17:23.292
but I'd like to dedicate
this award to a true friend,

17:23.668 --> 17:27.713
who started me on a path of service
to all Trolls‐manity,

17:27.713 --> 17:31.551
by confronting me
over a re‐gifted cupcake dome.

17:33.386 --> 17:34.887
‐ Well, that settles it, then.

17:35.263 --> 17:37.098
I'm going to talk to Dante.

17:37.098 --> 17:39.809
‐ Hold up. Better double‐check
your math, sis'.

17:39.809 --> 17:42.270
'Cuz according to my calculations,

17:42.270 --> 17:45.648
if Biggie confronts Dante,
this'll be what'll happen.

17:46.816 --> 17:50.528
‐ My… my word, Biggie.
I'm so embarrassed.

17:50.528 --> 17:53.781
I‐‐ I seem to be having
trouble looking you in the eye,

17:53.781 --> 17:55.658
I‐‐ I must go.

17:55.658 --> 17:56.867
[ Dante crying ]

17:57.410 --> 17:59.245
‐ Oh, my! That went horribly!

17:59.662 --> 18:02.748
‐ And from there,
things could only get worse.

18:03.541 --> 18:07.962
‐ Biggie, Dante, due to your claim
of irreconcilable awkwardness,

18:08.296 --> 18:10.756
I have no choice
but to declare your friendship

18:11.424 --> 18:12.550
null and void…

18:13.342 --> 18:14.343
Null and void…

18:14.927 --> 18:15.803
Null and void…

18:16.178 --> 18:18.598
‐ Sorry, this thing
glitches out sometimes.

18:19.015 --> 18:22.810
‐ Ah! Well, now I have no idea
whose advice to take.

18:23.019 --> 18:24.604
They both seem right!

18:24.604 --> 18:28.816
‐ But, Biggie, the data clearly shows‐‐
‐ My math is flawless, Biggie‐‐

18:29.442 --> 18:30.860
‐ No! Please!

18:30.985 --> 18:33.904
I'm very grateful to you both,
but I need time to think.

18:35.990 --> 18:37.033
‐ Null and void…

18:37.033 --> 18:37.825
Null and void…

18:37.825 --> 18:38.951
Null and void…

18:38.951 --> 18:39.994
Null and void…

18:39.994 --> 18:42.997
♪

18:49.128 --> 18:50.129
‐ A gift basket?

18:50.338 --> 18:51.130
From Biggie?

18:51.339 --> 18:52.340
BIGGIE:
<i>Dear R.</i>

18:52.465 --> 18:55.885
<i>I wanted you to know</i>
<i>that I've decided to take your advice</i>

18:55.885 --> 18:57.386
<i>and I wanted to say thank you.</i>

18:57.803 --> 19:00.931
<i>You've really given me perspective</i>
<i>and I appreciate your help.</i>

19:00.931 --> 19:02.183
<i>Regards, Biggie.</i>

19:02.600 --> 19:03.684
‐ Aww.

19:06.687 --> 19:07.813
[ R gasps ]

19:09.231 --> 19:11.484
Hey there, sibling supreme.

19:11.484 --> 19:15.404
Listen, I just want you to know
that I'm sorry we disagreed.

19:15.821 --> 19:17.698
I was just trying to do right by Biggie.

19:17.990 --> 19:19.033
‐ Me too.

19:19.033 --> 19:21.285
I know we both just want
what's best for him.

19:21.452 --> 19:22.870
‐ We really do.

19:23.454 --> 19:25.873
And hopefully, with time,

19:25.873 --> 19:29.835
you'll see that he made the right choice
by taking my advice.

19:30.044 --> 19:30.836
‐ Hold up!

19:32.004 --> 19:34.715
Biggie just told me
he's going to take my advice!

19:35.007 --> 19:36.425
I even got a fruit basket!

19:36.884 --> 19:39.053
‐ But he just told me…

19:39.887 --> 19:42.848
Excuse me! I gotta make sure
Biggie's talking to Dante!

19:42.848 --> 19:46.268
‐ No, I gotta make sure
he's not talking to Dante!

19:47.186 --> 19:48.896
♪

19:48.896 --> 19:50.648
♪ Gotta beat the clock ♪

19:50.940 --> 19:52.566
♪ Gonna set the pace ♪

19:52.900 --> 19:53.901
♪ Gotta stay on top ♪

19:53.901 --> 19:56.654
♪ Gotta come in first
I'm winning this race ♪

19:56.654 --> 19:58.280
♪ Never slowing up ♪

19:58.531 --> 20:00.491
♪ Never backing down ♪

20:00.491 --> 20:01.742
♪ You ain't keeping up ♪

20:01.742 --> 20:03.953
♪ No, I'm stronger, faster
Wearing you out ♪

20:03.953 --> 20:05.162
♪ Ooh ♪

20:05.162 --> 20:07.164
♪ Can't get past ♪

20:07.164 --> 20:09.041
♪ Way out front ♪

20:09.041 --> 20:10.918
♪ Not so fast ♪

20:10.918 --> 20:13.045
♪ Nah, nah, ooh ♪

20:13.045 --> 20:14.922
♪ Never last ♪

20:14.922 --> 20:16.841
♪ Always first ♪

20:16.841 --> 20:18.718
♪ Not so fast ♪

20:18.718 --> 20:20.886
♪ Not so fast ♪♪

20:21.303 --> 20:22.638
‐ Biggie, wait!

20:22.638 --> 20:24.098
‐ Don't talk to‐‐!
‐ Hey, guys!

20:25.266 --> 20:26.308
BOTH:
Poppy?

20:26.851 --> 20:29.353
‐ But, Biggie, I thought
you were gonna take my advice

20:29.353 --> 20:32.148
and express how you felt
about the re‐gift?

20:32.523 --> 20:33.482
‐ I am!

20:33.482 --> 20:36.277
'Cuz you were right,
I can't ignore my feelings.

20:36.277 --> 20:37.945
But you were also right.

20:37.945 --> 20:41.031
I don't want to embarrass Dante
if I don't have to.

20:41.157 --> 20:43.701
‐ So he expressed
his feelings to me, instead!

20:43.993 --> 20:47.913
‐ So, you took both of our advice?

20:47.913 --> 20:50.291
‐ And came up with a third option?

20:50.291 --> 20:52.293
‐ Yes! And I'm glad I did!

20:52.293 --> 20:56.756
Because by talking things out with Poppy,
I learned something very important…

20:56.922 --> 20:58.924
‐ The cupcake dome was from me!

20:59.091 --> 21:00.301
BOTH:
Say what?

21:00.760 --> 21:04.722
‐ Yeah, I went a little overboard
and gave two friend‐iversary gifts.

21:04.889 --> 21:08.017
‐ So Poppy just so happened
to give you a cupcake dome

21:08.017 --> 21:11.145
that was just like the one
you gave Dante last week?

21:11.312 --> 21:12.104
BOTH:
Mm‐hm.

21:12.271 --> 21:15.232
‐ But then what happened
to the friend‐iversary gift

21:15.232 --> 21:16.650
Dante gave you?

21:17.026 --> 21:17.985
‐ Hmm…

21:17.985 --> 21:18.778
DINKLES:
Mew.

21:19.653 --> 21:20.571
[ Biggie gasps ]

21:20.571 --> 21:22.573
‐ Mr. Dinkles! Really?

21:22.990 --> 21:24.033
‐ Wow!

21:24.033 --> 21:26.660
I guess we were both so preoccupied

21:26.660 --> 21:29.538
trying to find the answer
to Biggie's problem that…

21:29.538 --> 21:33.375
‐ We never considered there might be
more than one way to solve it.

21:33.542 --> 21:35.377
‐ Probably a good thing
to keep in mind

21:35.377 --> 21:37.630
when giving advice
in the future, huh, sis?

21:37.630 --> 21:39.048
‐ Oh, we will!

21:39.048 --> 21:39.924
'Cuz…

21:41.425 --> 21:43.135
BOTH:
R&B are on it!

21:44.220 --> 21:45.429
BOTH:
Aww!

21:47.515 --> 21:48.933
‐ Oh, that's right!

21:49.016 --> 21:50.851
I got you three gifts.

21:51.185 --> 21:52.102
[ Poppy laughs ]

21:56.190 --> 21:57.817
‐ Hello, you're on the hair!

21:58.067 --> 22:01.237
‐ Yes, I fear that I have broken
a beloved cupcake dome

22:01.237 --> 22:03.072
that was given to me by a dear friend.

22:03.656 --> 22:06.784
Do I replace it? Tell him what happened?
Change my identity?

22:06.784 --> 22:08.410
Oh, what does one do?

22:09.119 --> 22:11.247
‐ Easy, caller, we're here to help.

22:11.247 --> 22:13.249
But we need to take our time.

22:13.415 --> 22:16.377
‐ Yeah, 'cuz there are many ways
to approach this problem

22:16.377 --> 22:20.130
and we wanna find the solution
that works best for you.

22:21.006 --> 22:23.050
‐ R, B, you gotta help!

22:23.342 --> 22:25.803
‐ What is it?
‐ Something wrong with Two‐per?

22:26.011 --> 22:28.430
‐ Oh, no, no, Two‐Per is fine!

22:28.430 --> 22:31.767
My problem is with Twenty‐Nine‐per!

22:32.059 --> 22:35.062
[ Coopers laughing ]

22:37.064 --> 22:38.065
I can't take it!

22:38.065 --> 22:40.442
♪ No, keep the cat in the bag ♪

22:40.442 --> 22:42.653
♪ Ooh, we gotta bury the rag ♪

22:42.653 --> 22:44.488
♪ Ooh, or it's gonna be bad ♪

22:44.488 --> 22:46.824
♪ So let's get moving
'Fore they understand ♪

22:46.824 --> 22:49.243
♪ Let's stop the presses ♪

22:49.243 --> 22:51.078
♪ Ring the bell ♪

22:51.412 --> 22:52.746
♪ I confess ♪

22:52.746 --> 22:55.708
♪ It's not gonna end well ♪

22:55.708 --> 22:57.835
♪ Stop the presses ♪

22:57.835 --> 22:59.795
♪ Blow the horn ♪

23:00.129 --> 23:01.171
♪ You could guess ♪

23:01.171 --> 23:05.217
♪ It's worse than I could warn ♪♪
